  "voiceover": "Did the Church invent Jesus as God at the Council of Nicaea? It's a popular myth — helped along by novels — but the history is clear. Belief in Jesus' divinity is already there decades earlier, in the earliest layers of the New Testament. Paul, writing in the 50s, calls Jesus 'in very nature God' — Philippians 2:6. So what did Nicaea actually do? It didn't vote Jesus into divinity. It defended the language that protected what Christians already believed and worshipped, against a teaching that denied it. Not invented. Confessed.",
